<div id="review_988961563" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/988961563" />
    <a title="Idarah" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1283951-idarah"><img alt="Idarah" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1621951086p2/1283951.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/988961563?book_show_action=true">Jul 07, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Idarah" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Idarah" href="/user/show/1283951-idarah">Idarah</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781439165652" href="/book/show/9895914-the-hundred-foot-journey">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer988961563" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6996237602165598674">This book was such a delight to read, or rather listen to! If you&apos;re looking for a feel good book that makes you laugh and your tummy rumble, then this might be the book for you. I am by no means a gourmand, but I love reading about food adventures, and especially about how food unites peoples and cultures. <br/><br/>The strange events that lead Hassan Haji from his family owned restaurant on the Mumbai coast to the French Alps is the backdrop of this quaint novel. Tutored at a young age in the art of coo</span>
  <span id="freeText6996237602165598674" style="display:none">This book was such a delight to read, or rather listen to! If you're looking for a feel good book that makes you laugh and your tummy rumble, then this might be the book for you. I am by no means a gourmand, but I love reading about food adventures, and especially about how food unites peoples and cultures. <br /><br />The strange events that lead Hassan Haji from his family owned restaurant on the Mumbai coast to the French Alps is the backdrop of this quaint novel. Tutored at a young age in the art of cooking by his grandmother, Hassan inherits an artist's eye for flavoring and exotic food combinations. <a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[Before he knows it, he's on his way to becoming one of the most sought after chefs in Paris! <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span> While magical realism plays a key role in foodie fiction favorites like <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/47401.Chocolat__Chocolat___1_" title="Chocolat (Chocolat, #1) by Joanne Harris" rel="nofollow noopener">Chocolat</a> and <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/6952.Like_Water_for_Chocolate" title="Like Water for Chocolate by Laura Esquivel" rel="nofollow noopener">Like Water for Chocolate</a>, the plausible storyline of this novel made it more of an original little treat. Moreover, the marriage of two completely different cultures put me in mind of how well done <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/2967752.The_Elegance_of_the_Hedgehog" title="The Elegance of the Hedgehog by Muriel Barbery" rel="nofollow noopener">The Elegance of the Hedgehog</a> was, and also why the French are so stinking cool! I cannot wait to watch this film. I am a die hard Helen Mirren fan! <br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="6996237602165598674" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


