<span id="freeTextContainer422629950388573620">I had heard a lot about this book, and considering its about food and focuses on an Indian boy&apos;s journey into French cuisine, I thought it would be interesting. <br/>Unfortunately, I couldn&apos;t relate to it at all. The initial few chapters started off nicely, but after that the author just jumped from one point to another abruptly. Even though the title character was Indian belonging to a Muslim family, there was nothing that I felt I could relate - neither in terms of culture or food or traditions.<br/>Had</span>
